article.headline: Buffalo 73, Central Michigan 59
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Calvin Cage scored 17 points to lead Buffalo past Central Michigan 73-59 on Saturday. Buffalo (16-8, 6-7 Mid-American) built a 15-point lead in the first half, in which Cage scored 12 points -- all on 3-pointers. The Bulls went into halftime with a 39-26 advantage. Central Michigan (3-18, 1-12) cut the lead to seven points midway through the second half after a Sefton Barrett rebound and bucket. However, the Chippewas could get no closer as the Bulls hit their free throws down the stretch, going 19-for-23 from the line in the game and ending a four-game losing streak. The Bulls also connected on 10 of 20 shots from behind the 3-point line, while the Chippewas were just 3-for-22. Central Michigan's Sefton Barrett led all scorers with 24 points and nine rebounds, while Giordan Watson had 15 points and tied a career high with five steals. Buffalo changed its starting lineup by starting three players who had not started a game the entire season -- Christian Schmidt, Andy Robinson and Eric Moore. All three finished the game without scoring. Mario Jordan added 16 points for Buffalo, while Yassin Idbihi and Roderick Middleton each scored 12 and Sean Smiley added 10. Idbihi also came up with 10 rebounds.
